<br>
I never soloed much through all the levels.  But I've charm soloed (can be risky but if you find the right mobs--low resist or practice you can do it very well), used an animation (don't bother, the DPS is low and you can't control them until after 60 with AA abilities=too slow), and tried to play a druid/wizzie (dots and dd=also way too slow).  Dire charm is pretty good especially if you have the ability to heal the pet but that isn't soloing i guess.<br>
<br>
But with the changes to xp, WHY.  Even before I found soloing boring and only did it to finish off a level or when no one I knew was on.  Groups NEED us.  And we NEED groups.  You will get FAR more xp grouped than solo.  Make friends with every cleric you can.  Learn to play in group situations and you will be asked for groups all the time.  Can't remember the last time I soloed except to do quest shit though, just isn't worth my time.<br>
<br>
